724248f-a.text:
Water Street, south from Beekman to Fulton Streets. At the latter point is the low sloping roofed structure housing the old Brown Pharmacy. To the right appears the easterly side of Beekman Hospital (Volunteers of America). Note the 60 Wall Tower and the City Bank Farmers Trust bulldings in the background.
1939
Gift of Beecher Ogden

724247f-a.text:
Water Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of Beekman Street, also shown is Beekman Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Water Street.
About 1916.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
